\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 24. A. circinnatum} Sieber, {\i Reise Kreta }{\b 2}: 316 (1823). Bulbs 0·7 cm in diameter, ovoid; outer tunics chartaceous, pitted. Stem 5-18 cm, terete, hairy. Leaves 2-5, up to 24 cm × 1-1·5 mm, almost basal, linear, twisted or coiled especially at the apex into up to 10 coils, covered with long, patent hairs. Spathe 6-10 mm, 1-valved, 1- or 2-lobed at the apex, about as long as pedicels, persistent. Umbel fastigiate, with 2-5 flowers; pedicels 3-11 mm. Perianth stellate; segments 5-6 × 1·5-2 mm, white, with pink mid-vein, the outer oblong, the inner lanceolate, acute or obtuse. Stamens included; filaments c. 4 mm, simple; anthers yellow. Capsule 3 mm. Flowering March-April. {\i Dry, stony hillsides. • Kriti.} Cr.
