\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 27. A. breviradium} (Halácsy) Stearn,{\i  Ann. Mus. Goulandris}{\b  4}: 138 (1978) ({\i A. neapolitanum }var.{\i  breviradium} Halácsy). Bulbs 1·5-2 cm in diameter, ovoid; outer tunics membranous, not pitted. Stem 30-35 cm, slightly angled. Leaves 2-4, up to 24 cm × 10 mm, sheathing the lower 1/6 of the stem and almost basal, linear. Spathe 1-valved, 3- to 4-lobed, persistent, about as long as the pedicels. Umbel fastigiate, with 5-30 flowers, not bulbilliferous; pedicels 10-15 mm, almost equal. Perianth cylindrical campanulate; segments 9-12 × 3 mm, whitish, narrowly lanceolate, acuminate. Stamens included; filaments 7 mm, simple. Capsule 4 mm. •{\i  Mountains of S. Albania, S. Jugoslavia and N.C. Greece.} Al Gr Ju.
