\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 29. A. longanum} Pamp.,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Ital.}{\b  1912}: 116 (1912). Bulbs 0·8-1·5 cm in diameter, ovoid; outer tunics membranous, not pitted. Stem 15-42 cm, terete. Leaves 2-3, up to 30 cm × 3-8 mm, linear, sparsely or profusely ciliate. Spathe up to 1·5 cm, 1-valved, often 2-lobed, persistent, a little shorter than pedicels. Umbel 2-4·5 cm in diameter, fastigiate, with 6-25 flowers; pedicels 8-20 mm. Perianth campanulate, segments white, pink-tinged, narrowly oblong, unequal, the outer 7-12 × 4·5-6 mm, the inner 6-10 × 3-4·5 mm, truncate-rounded and emarginate at apex. Stamens included; filaments unequal, the outer 3·5-4·5 mm, the inner 5-6·5 mm, narrowly triangular; anthers yellow. Capsule 4 mm. {\i S. Aegean region} ({\i Kriti, Sirna, Astipalaia}). Cr Gr. ({\i Cyrenaica, Egypt}.)
