\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. A. subhirsutum} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 295 (1753) ({\i A. clusianum} Retz.). Bulbs up to 1·5 cm in diameter, subglobose; tunic membranous, not pitted. Stem 7-30 cm, terete. Leaves 2-3, 6-45 cm × 2-10 mm, almost basal, linear, ciliate. Spathe up to 1·3 cm, 1-valved, persistent, shorter than pedicels. Umbel 2·5-7 cm in diameter, hemispherical and lax, or fastigiate; pedicels up to 40 mm, 3-5 times as long as the perianth-segments, irregularly patent. Perianth stellate; segments 7-9 mm, white, lanceolate to oblanceolate, obtuse to acute. Stamens 1/2-2/3 as long as perianth; filaments 4-6 mm, subulate, simple; anthers usually brown, occasionally yellow. Capsule 3 mm. 2n = 14, 28.{\i  Rocky or sandy places. Mediterranean region.} Bl Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Sa Si [Az].
